element.name: Z is for Zoo by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: Dublin Zoo has long been a major attraction - moving with the times has not always been easy, given funding difficulties and the changes in public opinion regarding zoos and circuses as entertainment, yet it is still a popular venue.
element.encoded-hints: Vertical corner post, in the hedge!

ul.li:
2010-06-17T19:00:00Z : Found it by RoobyDoo
A quick cache before entering the wonderful zoo. Thanks for the cache. RD

2010-06-15T19:00:00Z : Found it by Ulyxes&Evasek
Really nice cache and also surrounding park.Well hidden, we spent some time to find it without GPS navigator.Thank you.

2010-06-12T19:00:00Z : Found it by Petr Skacha
Nice micro, our 60th cache.[:)] TFTC

2010-06-02T19:00:00Z : Found it by Ginblue
Got this in on the last day of our sort break in Dublin before returning to Wales. Finding the cache was not the problem, doing so in such a crowd was! So we just acted like the tourists we were, fiddling about with maps, GPS and note books. Loved Dublin. TFTC Ginblue

2010-06-02T19:00:00Z : Found it by eve1987
Not so easy with the hundreds of people :D The man from the entrance would think we are stupid ;)
TFTC and kind regards from Austria, eve

2007-08-19T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
Oh, so this is where the zoo is - looks a lot more modern than I've been told... must go there one day!
Found with Toadster and Cam. Stealth required but easy to hide amongst the crowds on this glorious afternoon.
